            "body": "Here's a hack that implements Phase 1, for those that want to see how it feels. (TODO: we could make it even more ergonomic to enter/focus the unfocused pager by temporarily mapping `<Enter>` or something like that).\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua\nindex 775af9077fbc..b9cd4966d8eb 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/_extui/messages.lua\n@@ -468,7 +468,18 @@ function M.set_pos(type)\n \n       -- It's actually closed one event iteration later so schedule in case it was open.\n       vim.schedule(function()\n-        api.nvim_set_current_win(win)\n+        vim.on_key(function(key, typedkey)\n+          if not typedkey then\n+            return\n+          end\n+          if win == api.nvim_get_current_win() then\n+            return\n+          elseif api.nvim_win_is_valid(win) then\n+            api.nvim_win_set_config(win, { hide = true })\n+            vim.on_key(nil, ext.bufs.msg) -- Delete this handler.\n+          end\n+        end, ext.bufs.msg)\n+\n         api.nvim_create_autocmd({ 'WinEnter', 'CmdwinEnter', 'CmdwinLeave' }, {\n           callback = function(ev)\n             -- Make pager relative to cmdwin when it is opened, restore when it is closed.\n@@ -498,4 +509,14 @@ function M.set_pos(type)\n   end\n end\n \n+vim.keymap.set('n', 'g<', function()\n+  local win = ext.wins.pager\n+  local cfg = api.nvim_win_is_valid(win) and api.nvim_win_get_config(win)\n+  cfg.hide = false\n+  if cfg then\n+    api.nvim_set_current_win(win)\n+    api.nvim_win_set_config(win, cfg)\n+  end\n+end)\n+\n return M\n```",
