        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I may have misinterpreted this issue until now. I thought phase 1 would mean always opening the (inactive) pager, rather than adding a spill indicator to the message in the cmdline. This I would consider a regression in terms of intrusiveness, which is why I've been hesitant on starting to implement it (besides working on other stuff).\n\nReading it again I realize this may not have been your intention @justinmk. I agree that entering the pager doesn't need to happen implicitly for the messages that we now route to it because we _do_ want to show them in full. Does #34679 address phase 1?",
