            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I agree that entering the pager doesn't need to happen implicitly for the messages that we now route to it because we _do_ want to show them in full. Does [#34679](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34679) address phase 1?\n\nYeah, Phase 1 is essentially implemented now, and it feels great, thank you @luukvbaal !🙏\n\nI encourage everyone to try it for a few days. We may be able to further refine some things, but I don't see a reason to ever focus the pager unless the user explicitly requests it.\n\nSome potential refinements:\n\n1. Make sure we always show the cmdheight-sized \"spill\" message even after the `on_key`, in case users \"accidentally\" dismiss the pager.",
